PERMITTED ACTIVITIES
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Without further permission, any person or entity obtaining a copy of the
Software may:

  (a) Read, examine, and audit the source code for security,
      correctness, educational, and research purposes.

  (b) Execute the mathematical verification scripts in the
      "verification/" directory to independently reproduce the stated
      curve properties.

  (c) Run the Software locally for the purpose of testing or
      personal evaluation, provided no derived cryptographic material
      is used for commercial purposes.

  (d) Cite, reference, and quote excerpts of the Software for academic
      publication, provided proper attribution is given to
      AncientHoldings GmbH and the Ouro-Network project.

  (e) Integrate the Software with other StoaChain / Ouro-Network
      products when authorised by a separate written agreement with
      AncientHoldings GmbH.

